# Ascendo — package exclusions (custom per-user opt-out).
#
# Lines: <category>:<package>     → pin/skip during apply phases
#        <category>:* (asterisk)  → skip the entire category for this user
#        '#' starts a comment.
#
# Categories: apt | snap | brew | npm | pip | flatpak | drivers
#
# Effect:
#   • apply phases for the listed packages are SKIPPED (kept on current ver).
#   • Inventory still reports them so you see they exist but won't be touched.
#   • Edit via UI (Apps tab → ✗ exclude) or directly.
#
# Example:
#   apt:firefox            # never auto-upgrade firefox
#   snap:slack             # I roll back manually if a release is bad
#   brew:*                 # don't touch brew at all
